import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['net_generation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['source', 'year']).sum().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.set_palette("husl")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="year", y="net_generation", hue="source", data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Net Generation')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum')
    ax = sns.heatmap(data, cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt='.2f', linewidths=.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Year')
    plt.title('What is the total net generation by year and source?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
